SauceDemo - E-commerce Test Automation Framework
https://img.shields.io/badge/Java-11%252B-blue
https://img.shields.io/badge/Selenium-4.15.0-green
https://img.shields.io/badge/TestNG-7.8.0-red
https://img.shields.io/badge/Cucumber-BDD-brightgreen
https://img.shields.io/badge/Maven-Build%2520Tool-orange
https://img.shields.io/badge/WebDriverManager-5.6.0-lightgrey

A professional test automation framework for e-commerce applications built with Java, Selenium, TestNG, and Cucumber following industry best practices.

🌐 Application Under Test
URL: https://www.saucedemo.com/

Credentials:

Username: standard_user

Password: secret_sauce

The Sauce Labs Demo site includes full e-commerce functionality with login, product browsing, cart management, and checkout - perfect for automation testing practice.

🚀 Features
Page Object Model (POM) design pattern for maintainable code

Behavior-Driven Development (BDD) with Cucumber for business-readable tests

Data-Driven Testing with TestNG DataProvider

Automatic Screenshot Capture on test failures

Cross-Browser Testing support via WebDriverManager

Professional Reporting with TestNG and Cucumber HTML reports

🛠️ Technologies Used
Technology	Version	Purpose
Java	11+	Programming language
Selenium WebDriver	4.15.0	Browser automation
TestNG	7.8.0	Test framework
Cucumber	7.14.0	BDD implementation
WebDriverManager	5.6.0	Automated driver management
Maven	3.6+	Build automation
🏗️ Project Structure
text
src/test/
├── java/
│   ├── pageObjects/          # Page classes following POM
│   │   ├── LoginPage.java
│   │   ├── ProductsPage.java
│   │   └── CartPage.java
│   ├── stepDefinitions/      # Cucumber step definitions
│   │   └── AddToCartSteps.java
│   ├── testCases/           # Test classes
│   │   ├── LoginTest.java
│   │   └── TestRunner.java
│   └── utilities/           # Helper classes
│       └── TestListener.java
└── resources/
    └── features/            # Cucumber feature files
        └── AddToCart.feature
⚙️ Installation & Setup
1. Prerequisites
Java JDK 11 or higher

Maven 3.6 or higher

Chrome browser (default) or other supported browsers

2. Clone and Install
bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd SeleniumCraft
mvn clean install
🧪 Running Tests
Run all tests
bash
mvn test
Run only Login tests
bash
mvn test -Dtest=LoginTest
Run Cucumber tests
bash
mvn test -Dtest=TestRunner
Run with specific browser
Modify the browser in the @BeforeMethod setup (default is Chrome).

📊 Test Cases
Successful Login - Valid credentials authentication

Invalid Login - Various invalid login scenarios (data-driven)

Add to Cart - BDD scenario for product cart functionality

📝 Sample Test - Login with Valid Credentials
java
@Test
public void testSuccessfulLogin() {
    loginPage.loginToApplication("standard_user", "secret_sauce");
    Assert.assertEquals(productsPage.getPageTitle(), "Products", 
            "Login was not successful or Products page title is incorrect");
}
📝 Sample BDD Feature
gherkin
Feature: Shopping Cart Functionality

  Scenario: A logged-in user adds a product to the cart
    Given the user is logged in
    When the user adds the "Sauce Labs Backpack" to the cart
    Then the shopping cart icon should show a count of "1"
📊 Reporting
TestNG Reports: target/surefire-reports/index.html

Cucumber Reports: target/cucumber-reports.html

Screenshots: screenshots/ directory (on test failures)

🛠️ Framework Design
Page Object Model: Separates page logic from test scripts

BDD Approach: Business-readable feature files with Gherkin syntax

Data-Driven Testing: Multiple test scenarios with minimal code

Automatic Driver Management: WebDriverManager handles browser drivers

Failure Handling: Automatic screenshots on test failures

⚠️ Important Notes
This is a demo framework for educational purposes

Uses a publicly available test environment

No real transactions occur during testing

